# SugarCube 2 Conventions

## Variable Scopes

| Prefix | Type | Persistence | Example |
|--------|------|-------------|---------|
| `$foo` | Story variable | Saved, survives passages | `$playerName`, `$money` |
| `_foo` | Temporary variable | Passage-local, reset each passage | `_charId`, `_count` |
| `setup.foo` | Static data | Defined once, NOT saved | `setup.quests`, `setup.items` |
| `State.variables.foo` | JS access to `$foo` | Same as `$` | From inside `<<script>>` or JS files |
| `State.temporary.foo` | JS access to `_foo` | Same as `_` | From inside `<<script>>` |

**Rule:** Never mutate `setup.*` at runtime per save — it's shared across saves. Use `$` for save-bound state.

## Macro Closing Tags — CRITICAL

SugarCube 2 uses `<</macroName>>` for closing. **Do NOT use** SugarCube 1 style `<<endmacro>>`.

```twee
<<script>>...<</script>>      ✅ correct
<<endscript>>                  ❌ WRONG — will error
<<if>>...<</if>>               ✅
<<for>>...<</for>>             ✅
<<widget>>...<</widget>>       ✅
<<nobr>>...<</nobr>>           ✅
<<silently>>...<</silently>>   ✅
<<link>>...<</link>>           ✅
<<button>>...<</button>>       ✅
<<switch>><<case>><</switch>>  ✅
```

## `<<nobr>>` Inside Widgets — Common Pitfall

Widget definitions often start with `<<widget "x">><<nobr>>`. You **must** close both:

```twee
<<widget "foo">><<nobr>>
    <<set _x = $args[0]>>
    ...
<</nobr>><</widget>>     ✅ both closed

<<widget "foo">><<nobr>>
    ...
<</widget>>              ❌ <<nobr>> leaks to next widget/passage
```

## Core Macros

### Flow Control

```twee
<<if _cond>>...<<elseif _other>>...<<else>>...<</if>>
<<switch $state>><<case "a">>...<<case "b">>...<<default>>...<</switch>>
<<for _i to 0; _i lt 5; _i++>>...<</for>>
<<for _item range $array>>...<</for>>
```

### State

```twee
<<set $x = 5>>
<<set _y to "hello">>             /* "to" and "=" both valid */
<<set $arr.push(item)>>           /* mutating calls work inline */
<<run someJsFunction(arg)>>       /* pure JS, no output */
<<unset $x>>
```

### Output

```twee
<<= $expression>>                 /* raw HTML */
<<- $expression>>                 /* escaped */
$variable                         /* shortcut for <<= $variable>> */
```

### Navigation

```twee
<<goto "passageName">>            /* immediate redirect */
<<include "passageName">>         /* render passage inline */
<<link "Go">><<goto "next">><</link>>
<<link "Run">><<run doThing()>><</link>>
<<button "Save">><<run Save.autosave.save()>><</button>>
```

### Script

```twee
<<script>>
    setup.foo = {};
    State.variables.playerName = "Lily";
<</script>>
```

## Widget Definition

Widgets are reusable macros defined in passages tagged `widget`.

```twee
:: MyWidgets [widget]

<<widget "myWidget">><<nobr>>
    <<set _arg1 = $args[0]>>
    <<set _arg2 = $args[1] || "default">>
    ...
<</nobr>><</widget>>
```

Call from any passage: `<<myWidget "value" 42>>`

Arguments appear in `$args` array inside the widget.

## JS Macro Registration (from `.js` files)

```javascript
Macro.add('myMacro', {
  tags: null,                    // or ['subMacro'] for block macros
  handler() {
    const $args = this.args;
    const payload = $args[0];
    $(this.output).wiki(payload); // render SugarCube markup
    // OR: this.output.textContent = 'plain';
    // this.error('message')  for errors
  }
});
```

## Event Hooks

```javascript
$(document).on(':passagestart', function (ev) { ... });
$(document).on(':passagerender', function (ev) { ... });
$(document).on(':passageend', function (ev) { ... });
$(document).on(':storyready', function () { ... });
```

## Common Mistakes Agents Make

1. **`<<endscript>>`** — doesn't exist in SugarCube 2, use `<</script>>`
2. **Forgetting `<</nobr>>`** in widgets — layouts break silently
3. **Using `$` inside `<<script>>`** — should be `State.variables.foo`
4. **Mutating `setup.*` per save** — use `$` for save-scoped state
5. **Passage name with spaces/hyphens** — avoid; camelCase preferred
6. **Circular `<<include>>`** — causes infinite recursion
7. **Missing `<<set>>`** — writing `$x = 5` alone doesn't work; needs `<<set $x = 5>>`

## Passage Tags Used in This Project

| Tag | Meaning |
|-----|---------|
| `widget` | Contains widget definitions (loaded early) |
| `init` | Runs at game start (via `StoryInit` or manual) |
| `nobr` | Auto-applies `<<nobr>>` to entire passage |
| `bookmark` | Appears in bookmark menu |
| `no-history` | Doesn't appear in back/history |
